      "id": "PopularPost224073",
      "post_content": "My favourite pseudo-pacifism effect of all time is [Kirtar's Desire](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Kirtar's Desire). I like unconventional ways of saying \"enchanted creature can't attack or block\". This card requires a long-term mana investment to hold down the creature, so you're better off playing [Pacifism](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Pacifism) or [Bonds of Faith](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Bonds of Faith).",
      "posted_by": "Chamale",
